                    <p>Collecting pre-sales revenue is the best way to validate a product idea. Stripe makes it easy to set up one-time payments on a really simple static HTML site. In this tutorial, we will implement a pre-order button with Stripe so that our visitors can request to pre-order our awesome product.</p><hr><h3 id="create-an-html-landing-page">Create an HTML landing page </h3><p>First things first, we need a landing page that speaks to our target market. That means having, </p><ol><li>Description of our product </li><li>Value props as to what value the product will provide</li><li>A shiny payment button so we can securely collect payments</li></ol><p>Our lovely team at SaaSBase decided to build a super easy ready-to go project <a href="https://github.com/bdcorps/stripe-pre-order">here</a> that you can use. Feel free to use it however you like, for personal or for commercial purposes. </p><figure><img src="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/web-1.png" alt="" srcset="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w600/2020/07/web-1.png 600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1000/2020/07/web-1.png 1000w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1600/2020/07/web-1.png 1600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/web-1.png 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"></figure><p>It include a Headline and a Sub-Headline that you can edit to match your offering. And most importantly it contains a Pre-Order button that when clicked should trigger the Stripe payment process. </p><pre><code>&lt;button	class="btn btn-outline-secondary"
    type="submit"
    id="order-btn"&gt; Pre-Order for $20&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre><h3 id="sign-up-for-stripe-account">Sign up for Stripe account</h3><p>Create a new Stripe account <a href="https://dashboard.stripe.com/register">here</a>. </p><figure><img src="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/1-1-1.png" alt="" srcset="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w600/2020/07/1-1-1.png 600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1000/2020/07/1-1-1.png 1000w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1600/2020/07/1-1-1.png 1600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/1-1-1.png 1897w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 1200px"></figure><p>A newly created Stripe account is put into <code>Test Mode</code> by default. This makes it easier to test the payment system without actually getting charged. Switch your account to <code>Live Mode</code> once you are ready to move to Production. For more information on Stripe's Test vs. Live Mode, <a href="https://stripe.com/docs/keys#test-live-modes">click here</a>. </p><p>Add a name for your account by clicking the <code>Add a name</code> button on the top left. </p><figure><img src="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/2-6.png" alt="" srcset="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w600/2020/07/2-6.png 600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1000/2020/07/2-6.png 1000w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1600/2020/07/2-6.png 1600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/2-6.png 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 1200px"></figure><h3 id="enable-client-only-integration">Enable Client-Only Integration</h3><p>Enable Client-Only Integration under Settings &gt; Checkout Settings.</p><figure><img src="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/3-2.png" alt="" srcset="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w600/2020/07/3-2.png 600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1000/2020/07/3-2.png 1000w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1600/2020/07/3-2.png 1600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/3-2.png 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 1200px"></figure><p><em>Note: Remember to add your hosting URL to Domains once you're live in Production to secure your payment gateway. </em></p><h3 id="create-a-product-on-stripe">Create a product on Stripe</h3><p>To add a new product, click on Products &gt; Add a New Product. Add a meaningful name, icon, and the price. Make sure to set the price to <code>One time</code>.</p><figure><img src="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/4-2.png" alt="" srcset="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w600/2020/07/4-2.png 600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1000/2020/07/4-2.png 1000w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1600/2020/07/4-2.png 1600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/4-2.png 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 1200px"></figure><p>Copy the <code>API ID</code> under Pricing.</p><figure><img src="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/5-1.png" alt="" srcset="https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w600/2020/07/5-1.png 600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1000/2020/07/5-1.png 1000w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/size/w1600/2020/07/5-1.png 1600w, https://saasbase.dev/content/images/2020/07/5-1.png 1920w" sizes="(min-width: 1200px) 1200px"></figure><p>Edit the Pre-Order button by pasting in the <code>API ID</code> from before. </p><pre><code> &lt;button
